  Ibid., p. 1085.
  Chester Finn is one such advocate.  For the success story 
see Barbara Lerner, "Good News About American Education," 
Commentary, March 1991, pp 19-25.
  James Q. Wilson, "Reforming the Schools," Commentary, 
Decem-ber 1991, pp. 57-62.
  Meyers, ed., The Mind of the Founder, p. 32.
* Compiled by Thomas G. West, University of Dallas.
* Editors' Note: The idea for this appendix arose during a 
November 1992 segment of the television interview show, 
"Meet the Press."  Its purpose, like that of Appendix A, is to 
demonstrate that Bible-based religious faith is perfectly 
compatible with the principles and traditions of American 
democracy.  Indeed, it is much more so than the facile 
moral relativism of modern liberals.

 

 




 

 

 

 

 

 


</DOC>
