<title>State Welfare Reform Conference - Heritage</title>
<body bgcolor="#FFFFFF" background="/heritage/paperh.jpg">
<blockquote>

<table border=0 width=600 cellspacing=6 cellpadding=6>
<tr>
<td><img src="/heritage/resource_bank/thflogo.gif" alt="The Heritage Foundation"></td><td><img src="/heritage/resource_bank/alec.gif" alt=American Legislative Exchange Council"></td></tr></table>

<p>
<center>				November 19, 1996</center>
<p>

Dear Colleague:
<p>
	It is our pleasure to invite you to the State Welfare Reform Conference cosponsored by The Heritage Foundation and the American Legislative Exchange Council (ALEC) from 7:30 a.m. to 5:30 p.m. December 5, 1996.  The conference will be held at the Renaissance Washington Hotel at 999 Ninth Street, N.W., Washington, DC.
<p>
	This forum will assemble hundreds of state legislators, executive branch officials, and think tank and business leaders from across the country to discuss policy ideas for states to manage the devolution of welfare.  Invited speakers include Virginia Governor <b>George Allen</b>, U.S. Representatives <b>James Talent</b> and <b>J.C. Watts</b>, California Social Services Director <b>Eloise Anderson</b>, Wisconsin Welfare Replacement Initiative Project Director <b>Jason Turner</b>, Heritage Senior Policy Analyst <a href="/heritage/staff/rector.htm"><b>Robert Rector</b></a>, American Institute for Full Employment Executive Director <b>Theodore Abram</b>, and National Center for Neighborhood Enterprise President <b>Robert Woodson</b>.  The conference immediately precedes the ALEC National Orientation Conference in the same hotel.
<p>
	There is no registration charge for the meeting and Heritage and ALEC will provide meals at no charge for all participants.  Please contact Nicole Brungard by telephone at (202) 546-4400, or send email to <a href="mailto:brungardn@heritage.org"> brungardn@heritage.org</a>.  Room reservations should be made directly with the Renaissance Washington Hotel at 202/898-9000.  We have secured a special conference rate of $154.  Also, there are additional rooms available at the Grand Hyatt at 202/582-1234 for $165 if you call before November 18.  Please keep in mind that registration for the ALEC National Orientation Conference (NOC) is separate.  If you are interested in attending the NOC, please contact Brad Boutilier at 202/466-3800.
<p>
	We look forward to seeing you at this important event!
<p>
					Sincerely,
<p>
