<HTML>
<HEAD>
<TITLE></TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY BGCOLOR="#008000" TEXT="#000000" LINK="#FFFF80" >
<A NAME = "TOP"> </A> 
<pre>
Resume
I am a Student of Social Sciences at the Georgia Augusta University of Goettingen, Germany. 
Before I started this internship, I spent an exchange year at SUNY Oswego, NY.
Although my field of studies is political science, I chosed to work for the Millennium Project
in the area of Economics and Wealth. My special interest was concentrated on the future of the
labor markets. Since that was the first time that I got involved into Future Studies, I had so
me difficulties to respond to a completely new way of thinking and doing research. I was 
sitting in the downtown office and kept track on futurist material in the internet.
Everything was very interesting, new, and exciting. It took me a while to distinguish between 
the serious stuff that mattered to me and the rather populistic ideas; but I red everything I 
could get (including soccer results from Germany).
In addition, I used the library at The American University, The United Nations Information 
Center, and some books and articles from Jerry's private library. 
I noticed that the longer I was occupied with this internship, the more I changed my attitude 
towards the future. As many of my friends at home, my general expectations of the future were 
pessimistic; but the more theories, ideas, and scenarios I investigated, the wider became the 
range of possible futures. I learned about possibilities that I never would have thought 
before. Now I am much more optimistic because I have a much wider variety of answers to the 
challenges of the future. 
The highlight, of course was attending the World Future Society Conference fom July 14th to 
July 18th 1996. 
</pre>
</HTML>
</body>

August 20, 1996
</DOC>
