<IMG SRC="l_hand.gif"> <A HREF="Millennium_Project.html">Millennium Project Home Page</A>

<HR>

<P>
<CENTER><A NAME="planet"><B>UNU GLOBAL SEMINAR '96 - KOBE SESSION</B>
<BR>
<B>&quot;OUR PLANET AND HUMAN SECURITY&quot;</B></A></CENTER>
<P>
The United Nations University (UNU) and the Kobe International
Association will organize jointly the Second Kobe Session of the
UNU Global Seminar, on the theme of &quot;Our Planet and Human
Security,&quot; from 1 to 4 October 1996 at the Hotel Pearl City
Kobe, Port Island, Kobe City.
<P>
The UNU has been organizing an annual UNU Global Seminar in the
Kanto area since 1985. The seminar focusing on a global issue
is mainly targeted to undergraduate and graduate students in Japanese
universities. From 1995, in commemoration of the United Nations'
50th and UNU's 20th anniversaries, a similar seminar series was
initiated also in the Kansai area, and the first &quot;Kobe Session&quot;
was held in September last year.
<P>
The UNU Global Seminar is designed to enhance international awareness
among the student population in Japan through active interaction
with scholars and experts working in UNU's global networks. Undergraduate
students, in their junior year and above, and those in postgraduate
courses in Japanese universities are eligible to apply. Applicants
must understand both Japanese and English languages. Approximately
50 students selected from the applicants will participate in a
four-day course.
<P>
In the Second Kobe Session, lecturers include Mr. Ingvar Carlsson,
former Prime Minister of Sweden (to be confirmed), Ms. Gertrude
Mogella, Secretary-General for the Fourth World Conference on
Women held in Beijing, China, last September, Professor Jun Nishikawa,
Waseda University, and Dr. Andrzej Wojtczak, Director, WHO Centre
for Health Development in Kobe. Please see the attached programme
for details.
<P>
The participation fee (including accommodations and meals) is
Yen30,000 which may be waived for students from developing countries.
Applications must be submitted to the UNU Global Seminar Secretariat
no later than 30 June 1996. Application forms are available from
the Secretariat.
<P>
* * *
<P>
For further information, please contact:
<P>
UNU Global Seminar &quot;Kobe Session&quot; Secretariat<BR>
Tel.: (078) 302-5200 (Mr. Koyama or Ms. Takeda)<BR>
Fax: (078) 302-6485<BR>
or<BR>
UNU Public Affairs Section<BR>
Tel.: (03) 5467-1243, -1246<BR>
Fax: (03) 3406-7346 <BR>

<P>
UNU Global Seminar '96 - Kobe Session<BR>
&quot;Our Planet and Human Security&quot;<BR>
1-4 October 1996 at Hotel Pearl City Kobe<BR>
______________________
<P>
Organized by: The United Nations University; and the Kobe International
Association<BR>
Supported by: Ministry of Foreign Affairs of Japan, Ministry of
Education, Science, Sports and Culture of Japan; Hyogo Prefectural
Government; Kobe Municipal Government; and the Kobe Chamber of
Commerce and Industry<BR>
Sponsored by: Amway Japan Limited; Kirin Brewery Co., Ltd.; Matsushita
Electric Industrial Corp. Ltd.; and Japan Airlines
<P>
