<P>
<CENTER><A NAME="BM1998NGO"><B>THE FIRST PREPARATORY MEETING OF
THE 1998<BR>
<B>WORLD NGO CONFERENCE AND AN INTERNATIONAL SYMPOSIUM</B></B></A></CENTER>
<P>
3 September 1996<BR>
PR/E12/96<BR>

<P>
To Be Held at the UNU Headquarters on 23 and 24 September 1996

<P>
The United Nations University (UNU), with the co-sponsorship of
the Tokyo Metropolitan Government and several international non-governmental
organizations (NGOs), will host the first preparatory meeting
for the planned 1998 World NGO Conference on 23 September and
an international symposium on 24 September, at the UNU Headquarters
International Conference Hall in Tokyo. The purpose of these sessions
is to discuss: the role of NGOs in an emergent global civil society
and new relationships between NGOs and the United Nations. 
<P>
Taking part in the preparatory meeting and the symposium will
be some 40 participants from around the world, including: NGO
leaders, eminent scholars, high-ranking UN officials and senior
representatives of international organizations. 
<P>
On 23 September there will be a half-day free discussion, which
is closed to the public, preparing for the planned 1998 World
NGO Conference in Tokyo. On 24 September there will be a full-day
public symposium on &quot;the United Nations and Civil Society.&quot;
Panelists will exchange views on: the changing role of NGOs and
civil society organizations working with the UN; experiences in
sectoral, regional and global approaches; and visions and actions
for the 21st century in UN/NGO relationships. 
<P>
A copy of the programme is attached. English-Japanese simultaneous
interpretation is available on 24 September only. 
<P>
Representatives of the news media are cordially invited to attend
both sessions. <BR>

<P>
For further information, please contact:<BR>
<BR>
UNU Public Affairs Section<BR>
Tel.: (03) 5467-1243,-1246<BR>
Fax: (03) 3406-7346<BR>
