<HTML>	<HEAD>		<TITLE>EARTH TRIBE</TITLE>	</HEAD><Body background="blue_paper.gif"><CENTER><IMG SRC="spine.gif"><IMG SRC="earthtr.gif"><H3><I>Universal Language of Music, Harmony Between all Races</H3></I></CENTER><P>	Here are a few media samples from the music adventure video <I>Earth Tribe L.A.</I>, a multi-cultural music documentary which was nominated for an L.A. Area Emmy Award.  <P><CENTER><A HREF="earthtr.html"><IMG SRC="earthfa.gif"> </A><P>View a <A HREF="earthtr.html">larger .jpg image</A> of the EARTH TRIBE cover photo. </A><P><font size="-2">Copyright 1994, Jason Klassi</font>	<hr size=5 width=10%><hr size=5 width=20%><P>  Here are two sample music clips from the music adventure video <I>Earth Tribe L.A.</I>.  The first clip is from the song <I>Tribes</I> which premiered in the United Nations General Assembly Hall at the kick-off celebration for the 1992 Earth Summit global environmental conference.</P><P><A HREF="tribes.wav"><I>Tribes</I> Chorus (221K .wav file)</A><P><font size="-2">Copyright 1994, Klassi/Bogdanovich</font><P>The second music clip is performed by Ayo, a master drummer from Nigeria.  What he says is as significant as what you will hear him play.  <P> <A HREF="africa.wav"><IMG SRC="ayo.gif"><P> Music from Nigeria (347K .wav file)</A></P><hr size=5 width=10%><hr size=5 width=20%></CENTER>Join filmmaker-composers Jason Klassi and Anna Thea Bogdanovich on a musical expedition of traditional cultures thriving in the urban jungles of Los Angeles, California.  Experience the primal rhythms and dance of Nigeria with Owun Ayo - Sounds of Happiness.  Feel the ancient power of Japan wth the young drummers of the Zenshuji Zendeko Taiko ensemble.  Visit an Inter-tribal Powwow where all races partake in the Native American Spirit.  Witness Aztec dancing accompanied by the magical Pre-Colombian music of Xavier Quijas "Yxayotl" - Shaman.  Finally, <I>Tribes,</I> a rock/worldbeat montage celebrates the multi-cultural diversity of our common global family, the "Earth Tribe".<P>If you like more information about the 30 minute <I>Earth Tribe L.A.</I> <A HREF="http://ddi.digital.net/~planet/nko/earthtrb.html"> VHS video, follow this link.</A><P><I>Earth Tribe L.A.</I> was produced by ROAD LESS TRAVELED MEDIA in association with EXPEDITION EARTH, INC., a 501(c)3 non-profit corporation.<P><hr size=5 width=10%><hr size=5 width=20%><P><CENTER><I>Two roads diverged in a wood, and I-<P>I took the one less traveled by,<P>And that has made all the difference.</I>     <P>Robert Frost </CENTER><P> <hr size=5 width=10%><hr size=5 width=20%><P></CENTER><CENTER><P><TABLE BORDER="2" CELLPADDING="2"><TR><TD><font size="-1"><A HREF="index.html"><B>Expedition Earth</A></B></FONT></TD><TD><font size="-1"><B>Earth Tribe media</A></B></FONT></TD><TD><font size="-1"><A HREF="http://nko.mhpcc.edu/tdp/"><B>The Daily Planet</B></A></FONT></TD><TD><font size="-1"><A HREF="taw.html"><B>Trees Around the World</A></B></TD></TR></TABLE><P><A HREF="index.html"><IMG SRC="earth.gif" ALIGN="middle"> Expedition Earth Home page</a>  <P><address><A HREF="mailto:wowla@earthlink.net">E-mail Expedition Earth</A></address></CENTER></body></html>January 17, 1996
