<HTML> 
<TITLE>Trees Around The World</TITLE> 
<body text=000000 link=#0000dd vlink=#0000dd bgcolor=a0ffa0>
<CENTER> 
<table border=5 cellpadding=3>
<tr><td width=288 height=112>
<img src="taw.gif" border=0>
</td></tr></table>
<p>
<FONT SIZE=6>TREES AROUND THE WORLD</font><br>
<FONT SIZE=4>AN INTERACTIVE INTERNATIONAL 
GATHERING OF THE TRIBES</font><p>
<H3>SUMMER 1996</H3><p>
</center>
<HR SIZE=4 WIDTH=60% ALIGN=CENTER><BR>
<center>
<blockquote><font size=4>People of all ages, cultures, and walks of life are invited to gather under trees around the world with family, friends, and other community members to promote a global vision of unity-in-diversity.  This global celebration and participatory event of one world family under one symbolic tree of life, pays tribute to our collective home, the Earth.  The use of a symbolic "Tree of Life" or "World Tree" has been consistantly represented in most ancient myths and cultures around the world.<P></font><p></center>
<CENTER>
<FONT SIZE=5>Focus Special Event 1995:</font> <BR> 
2nd Annual <B>TREES AROUND THE WORLD</B>
<P>
</CENTER>

TREES AROUND THE WORLD was a featured event of the 1995 <a href="partners.html"><i>Partners for the Planet</i></a> 1995 National Youth Summit, spearheaded by environmental youth organization, <a href="treemusk.html">TREE MUSKETEERS</a>.<P></BLOCKQUOTE>

<HR SIZE=4 WIDTH=80% ALIGN=CENTER><BR>

Many hundreds of years ago, after generations of bloodshed, five warring tribes were moved to unite in peace.  They buried their weapons under a great tree.<p>  

An opportunity arises to reclaim that vision around the world.<p>

A giant sequoia, the largest living tree on our planet, calls to us.  It is currently and appropriately named after a war hero, General Sherman.  There is a dream to unite around trees all over the world, and to bury our prejudices and hatred.<p>

The tree invites everyone: warriors and peacemakers; victims and aggressors; children and elders; the indifferent and the passionate, enemies and friends.  Under the shade of this tree we are all equal.  It has seen our ancestors come and go, and it will be here when we are gone.<p>

The dream is that today's children will live to see this tree, all the trees, in peace.</BLOCKQUOTE><p>

<HR SIZE=4 WIDTH=80% ALIGN=CENTER><BR>

<center>

SUGGESTIONS FOR ADDITIONAL ACTIVITIES AROUND A TREE OF YOUR CHOICE:<BR>MUSIC, STORYTELLING, TREE PLANTING, FAMILY REUNIONS, <BR>ENVIRONMENT/WORLD PEACE COUNCILS, PLAN AN EVENT, USE YOUR IMAGINATION.<br>

<HR SIZE=4 WIDTH=60% ALIGN=CENTER><BR>
<table border=0 width=50%>
<tr>
<td align=center>
<font size=4>TREES AROUND THE WORLD<BR> was inspired by the<BR>
<b>GENERAL SHERMAN TREE</b><BR>
world`s largest living thing,<BR>
2300-2700 years old<BR>
growing in the Giant Forest<BR>
Sequoia National Park, California, U.S.A.<p>
</td>
<td align=left>
<img src="sequoia.gif" height=200>
</td>
<tr>
</table>
<P>
<FONT SIZE=5>The second annual Trees Around the World event took place on July 9 in Snowbird, Utah as part of the <a href="partners.html"><i>Partners for the Planet</i></a>  1995 National Youth Summit</font>
<p>
<table border=5 cellpadding=3>
<tr><td align=center height=112>
<a href="partners.html"><IMG SRC="partners.gif" height=112 align=absmiddle border=0></a>
</td></tr>
</table>
<p>
<P>HOTLINE FOR SUMMIT INFO:  (800) 473-0263</font><p>
SPREAD THE WORD!!!  E-SEED THE VISION OF A WORLD AT PEACE
<P> 
