<i>The logo for the 1995 Partners for the Planet Youth Summit is the masterpiece of 17-year-old Mason Poe, an integral member of Kids F.A.C.E. Mason has served as a youth partner on the Executive Committee of the Youth Summits since the first one in 1993.  There is more to Mason's illustration than you may see at first.  If you look closely at the roots of the tree, you will notice that they are little children who give life to the united youth environmental movement.  This movement stretches out its arms to spread its message to the world through nature (butterflies).  The snowcapped mountains in the background represent Snowbird, Utah, the location of the '95 Youth Summit.</i><br>
