<P>
<A NAME="CROATIA">
<B>
10 December 1996
<BR>
PR/E23/96
<P>

<CENTER>
CROATIAN DEPUTY PRIME MINISTER TO GIVE LECTURE
AT THE UNITED NATIONS UNIVERSITY
</CENTER></A></B>

<P>
Mate Granic, Croatian Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of Foreign Affairs, will speak at
the United Nations University Headquarters from 16.45 to 17.55 hours on Tuesday, 
17 December 1996. Dr. Granic's lecture is titled "An Overview of Croatian Foreign Policy:
Priorities and Perspectives," and will include a discussion of Croatia's relationship with 
the European Union, the United Nations, and Japan.  Following his lecture, Dr. Granic will
answer questions from the audience.
<P>
Dr. Granic has served Croatia in many capacities since becoming Deputy Prime Minister in 
1991.  He was the Government's chief negotiations representative with the Yugoslav People's 
Army and was in charge of coordinating all incoming international humanitarian organizations.
He was also the chief Croatian negotiator in proceedings before the UN Security Council. 
Before entering politics, he was Dean of the University of Zagreb's Medical School.
<P>
Members of the media are cordially invited to attend his lecture. Simultaneous English-Japanese interpretation will be provided. 
<P>
<CENTER>* * * * *</CENTER>
<P>
<CENTER>For further information, please contact: <BR>
UNU Public Affairs Section <BR>
Tel.: (03) 5467-1243, -1246 <BR>
Fax: (03) 3406-7346</CENTER>
<P>
Yukiko Kobayashi <BR>
Public Affairs <BR>
United Nations University 
