<HEAD>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
<TITLE>Issue 6</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#96E1FA">

<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=5 FACE="Times New Roman">ISSUE 6</FONT><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">:
</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Times New Roman"> Terrorism is growing
in intensity, scale, and threat<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">With the bombings of the Olympics
in Atlanta, the New York World Trade Center, the Oklahoma City
Federal Building, and Pan American 103, and terrorist acts in
the Balkans, Somalia, Liberia, Colombia, and Japan terrorism is
now global, destructive, and difficult to prevent. <BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Within the last three years: Chechen
crime groups may have been involved in the theft of six kilograms
of enriched uranium recovered in Istanbul. The Czech Government
intercepted a shipment of 6.6 pounds of enriched uranium from
a nuclear smuggling ring; the German Government found six tenths
of a pound of plutonium in Munich on a Lufthansa plane from Moscow.
German authorities reported 276 nuclear smuggling incidents in
1994.   What is the destination of these materials?<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">The weapons that may become available
to terrorists, e.g. nuclear and biological weapons, and have become
available, e.g. chemical weapons and computer sabotage make the
threat particularly ominous. The arsenals of the United States,
Russia and many other nations contain biological and chemical
weapons that also have massive killing potential. The uses of
such weapons by terrorists is not hard to imagine - the subway
gas attack in Tokyo is a<B> </B>tragic example. These materials
need not be stolen since their manufacture requires easily obtainable
raw materials and conventional technology.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Possibilities for the future: extortion
against a government or corporation, retaliation by terrorists
for perceived insults, use by renegade governments or revolutionary
groups to achieve power. Technological terrorism, especially large&#173;scale
sabotage through the Internet, might lead to the call for a new
police role.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Times New Roman">Round 3 questions:  </FONT></B><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Please
use the scales shown in the instructions to provide your judgments
about the following actions. You are also welcome to add other
actions that you think are likely to be practical and effective.
<BR><BR>
</FONT>
<TABLE BORDER=1>

<TR><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=408><B><FONT FACE="WP MathB">Suggested Actions:</FONT></B>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=84><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Effectiveness</FONT>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Practicality</FONT>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=60><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Agency</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">1. At least double the amount of funding devoted to detection, capture and punishment of terrorists; perhaps shifting funds form conventional military to anti-terrorism. </FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">2. At least double the amount of funding devoted to protection against terrorists acts, such as airport security. </FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">3. Establish an open forum for discussion of issues that enflame terrorists.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">4. Toughen world wide penalties for convicted terrorists, including mandatory death sentences.  </FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">5. Tighten laws, regulations, and inspections associated with security of nuclear stocks. </FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">6. Develop protection strategies for biological attack.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">7. Destroy existing stockpiles of biological weapons.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">8. Expand coordination/cooperation of information and early warning, apprehension, and punishment of terrorists among nations that might not normally cooperate.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">9. Create social marking programs that promote respect and tolerance for ethnic and other forms of diversity.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">10. Plan to build resilience and redundancies into socio-technical systems to avoid possible catastrophic disruptions (including electronic infrastructures from info-terrorism).</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
