<HEAD>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
<TITLE>Issue 2</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#96E1FA">

<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=5 FACE="Times New Roman">ISSUE 2:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Times New Roman">
Fresh water is becoming scarce in localized areas of the world.
 <BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Lack of adequate waste management
in most places in the world; excessive consumption and contamination
of water aquifers; excessive farming on marginal lands, and population
and urbanization trends are affecting the availability &#173;
and future expectations of availability &#173; of fresh water.
The countries facing scarcity include: eleven African countries,
nine Middle Eastern countries, northern China (including Beijing
and the agricultural lands surrounding it); India (including New
Delhi and thousands of rural villages); Mexico (including Mexico
City and irrigated farmlands in northern Mexico); and portions
of the Western United States.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">While methods exist to purify salt
water, these methods are expensive. To further complicate the
situation, agricultural uses far exceed other uses of water and
with increased demand for food, pressure to use water for agriculture
can only increase. Agricultural land is being lost to brackish
conditions due to  long&#173;term geological trends in some regions.
The possibility, speed and consequences of global warming are
uncertain, but at the very least, changes in rainfall patterns
will undermine effectiveness of existing water control, storage
and distribution facilities, and widen areas affected by scarcity.
As population growth and urbanization proceed, competition between
urban and agricultural uses of water will grow.  <BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Times New Roman">Round 3 questions:  </FONT></B><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Please
use the scales shown in the instructions to provide your judgments
about the following actions. You are also welcome to add other
actions that you think are likely to be practical and effective.
<BR><BR>
</FONT>
<TABLE BORDER=1>

<TR><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=408><B><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Suggested Actions:</FONT></B>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=84><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Effectiveness</FONT>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Practicality</FONT>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=60><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Agency</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">1. Secure treaties and cooperative agreements on water rights between nations that share water resources before shortages occur.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">2. Develop water trading and marketing practices that allow users and managers to better allocate scarce supplies and fund conservation. </FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">3. Begin immediate research and development programs to produce means for producing inexpensive fresh water from salt water.(1) </FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">4. Encourage further development of plant strains and agricultural practices that uses salt or brackish water for irrigation, and/or are drought-harty.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">5.Establish a World Water Agency to develop and expedite new water technology and water extraction and collection projects. </FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">6.Establish water conservation policies and incentives to improve efficiency of water use.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>

</TABLE>

