<HTML>

<HEAD>

<META NAME="GENERATOR" CONTENT="Internet Assistant for Microsoft Word 2.0z">
<TITLE>Issue 4</TITLE>

</HEAD>

<BODY BGCOLOR="#96E1FA">

<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=5 FACE="Times New Roman">ISSUE 4:</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Times New Roman">
The Threat of New and Re-emerging Diseases and Immune Micro- 
organisms<BR>
<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Recent outbreaks of bubonic plague
in India, ebola virus in Africa, and drug-resistant tuberculosis
in America is causing the world to re-think its public health
policies.  Increasing mass migrations and international travel
spread disease more rapidly than in the past; increasing urbanization
and population density accelerate and intensify this issue. Furthermore,
the widespread use of antibiotics has resulted in the evolution
of micro-organisms that are resistant to antibiotics.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<FONT FACE="Times New Roman">&quot;Infectious diseases spreading
in US hospitals kill more each year than all Americans killed
in Vietnam...The heaviest concentration of pathogens is found
in the developing world...The progress of pathogens to adapt to
our arsenal of medicines promises to be the fight of our species...It
is a trend that holds the capacity to bring life as we know it
to a grinding halt...A handful of microbes can be stopped at the
boarder but the vast majority cannot,&quot; U.S. Congressional
testimony April 25, 1996 by Chuck Woolery, National Council for
International Health. In addition, the threat of biological terrorism
is now plausible.<BR>
</FONT>
<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=4 FACE="Times New Roman">Round 3 questions:</FONT><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">
 </FONT></B><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">Please use the scales
shown in the instructions to provide your judgments about the
following actions. You are also welcome to add other actions that
you think are likely to be practical and effective.<BR>
</FONT><BR>
<TABLE BORDER=1>

<TR><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=408><B><FONT FACE="WP MathB">Suggested Actions:</FONT></B>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=84><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Effectiveness</FONT>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Practicality</FONT>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=60><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Agency</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">1. Strengthen and expand the global network of WHO collaborating laboratories to create an effective global surveillance system for emerging viruses and infections.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">2. Create a rapid medical deployment capacity to respond to outbreaks of infectious disease with the epidemic potential. </FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">3. Training, credit, and technical assistance for small and micro-economic development to improve economic development in poorer countries and thus improve the standard of living.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">4. Strengthen the funding and capability of such agencies as CDC, USAID, WHO and other international technical agencies in order to better collaborate with countries in strengthening national disease surveillance and control systems.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">5.  Intensify programs that are designed to delay or slow urbanization.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">6. Focus international attention and funding on those diseases that have been targeted by the World Health Assembly for eradication or elimination as public health problems (polio, measles, guinea worm and leprosy).</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">7. Increase funding and technical support for the Global Programme on Vaccines to ensure maximum coverage is obtained with existing antigens and that research and development is intensified for other possible vaccines (such as for malaria).</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">8.  Initiate intensified research into second generation antibiotics.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


<TR><TD WIDTH=408><FONT FACE="Times New Roman">9.  Increase funding for safe water supply projects.</FONT>
</TD>
<TD WIDTH=84><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=72><BR></TD>
<TD WIDTH=60><BR></TD>
</TR>


</TABLE>

