<P>
<B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="CG Times">During Round 2 additional developments
were suggested.</FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="CG Times">  Those
that were related to this issue and were not repeated elsewhere
in this issue brief included: <UL><BR>
</FONT>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=3 FACE="CG Times">149. R &amp; D progress  is being
made in alternative energy sources,  such as  thermonuclear fusion
and solar energy. The seamless replacement of fossil fuels worldwide
is  projected for the long-term.   <BR>
</FONT>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Times New Roman">165. Possible losses of monoculture
crops because of unexpected pathogens (BTH).<BR>
</FONT>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Times New Roman">168. Continued expansion of
wind power (33% in 1995).<BR>
</FONT>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Times New Roman">169. More intense and violent
storms (from global warming?)<BR>
</FONT>
<LI>
<FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Times New Roman">179. The demands of the exponentially
growing global population for improved living standards are increasing
 the pressure to construct new fossil and nuclear power plants.
 However, encouraging progress is being made in the direct and
indirect conversion of solar energy into useful forms including
hydroelectric, photovoltaics, wind turbines, solar concentrators,
biomass, ocean thermal conversion and solar water heating.
</UL>
