in alternative energy sources,  such as  thermonuclear fusion
and solar energy.</FONT>

<LI><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Times New Roman">161. Threat from natural catastrophies
to nuclear stores, power plants, etc.</FONT>

<LI><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Times New Roman">172. Continued expansion of
wind power (33% in 1995).
</FONT>

<LI><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Times New Roman">174. Number of nuclear war
heads is dropping sharply as US &amp; former Soviet Union disarm,
but &quot;hedge' stockpiles are being planned.</UL><BR>

