1=almost certain; 5=almost impossible.  <BR><B>Importance scale</B>:
1=urgently important; 5=trivial</FONT><BR><BR>
<TABLE BORDER=1>

<TR><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=402><B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="Times New Roman">Related Developments </FONT></B><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">   </FONT>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Likelihood</FONT>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=78><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Importance</FONT>
</TD><TD BGCOLOR=#FFFFFF WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">Agency</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=402><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">24. High population growth among poor nations and people.</FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">1.42</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH=78><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">1.44</FONT></TD><TD WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">GOV</FONT>
<BR>
<FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">UNO</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=402><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">74.     The widening economic gap between the &quot;haves and the have&#173;nots&quot; within and between countries. </FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">1.58</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH=78><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">1.54</FONT></TD><TD WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">GOV</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=402><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">126. The uneven and unfair distribution of wealth among nations (north south divide) and also within nations.</FONT>
</TD><TD WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">1.54</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH=78><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">1.75</FONT></TD><TD WIDTH=72><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">UNO</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR><TD WIDTH=402><FONT SIZE=3 FACE="WP MathB">9.   Increasing apparent conflicts between economic and societal aims: economic measurement and incentives subvert social growth.</FONT>
