<center><font size=+1><i><b>Violence</b></i><p></font></center>

54. <b>Development:</b> Violence as a global problem. Sources, instruments, promotion and
exploitation of violence abound (movies, TV, drugs, fundamentalism, racism, terrorism).   <br>
<b>Potential Consequences:</b> increasing insecurity, destabilization of governments, social
disorder,
economic injustice, institutional and legal failure.<br>
<b>Goals:</b> Global approach to global violence; global institutions with real although limited
powers,
that control violence on its bases; education and  mass media supporting solidarity, negotiation,
peace
building in global scale, and peaceful conflict resolution through mediation and the rule of law.
<br>
<b>Domain:</b> 3, 4, 5 and 6 <br>
<b>References and Notes:</b> a) <i>Violence in America: A Public Health Approach.</i> Edited
by
Mark L. Rosemberg and Mary Ann Fenley. Oxford Univ. Press. N.Y., 1991. Violence is a law
enforcement problem but, at the same time, is a  welfare problem and a health problem.;  b) F.
Homer-Dixon, Jeffrey H. Boutwell, and George W. Rathgens, "Environmental Change and
Violent Conflict".
<i>Scientific American,</i> 268:2, Feb. 1991. Report of the project on Environmental Change
and Acute
Conflict,  sponsored by  the University of Toronto, Canada, and the American Academy of Arts
and
Sciences;  c) <i>Understanding and Preventing Violence.</i> Edited by Albert J. Reiss and Jeffrey
A.
Roth. Washington. National Academy of  Press. Report of the Panel on the Understanding and
Control of
Violent Behavior created by the National Academy of Sciences. Washington  D.C. National
Academy
Press. 1993. Needless to emphasize the importance of violence in Latin America: Mexico,
Colombia, El
Salvador, Guatemala, Nicaragua,  Peru, Bolivia, Argentina and Brazil are examples of different
kinds of
violence.                            <p>
                                  
103. <b>Development:</b> Introduction into military, police and terrorist arsenals of non-lethal
